wiki.text:
'FFD', 'Ffd' or 'ffd' may refer to:

* Fairfield railway station, Melbourne, Australia; station code FFD.
* Fall for Dance Festival at New York City Center
* Focus film distance, the distance between the X-ray source and the film in
  diagnostic radiography
* Flange focal distance, the distance from the mounting flange of a lens mount
  system to the film plane
* Front focal distance, the distance from the front focal point of the system to
  the vertex of the first optical surface
* Forward flank downdraft (sometimes front flank), in meteorology, the leading
  edge (downwind) downdraft of a supercell thunderstorm
* The IATA airport code for RAF Fairford
* FF Developments, a UK transmission engineering company
* Free-form deformation, a technique for manipulating any shape in a free-
  form manner.
